{{Infobox company | native_name = Enti Rregullator i Energjisë | native_name_lang = sq | name = Energy Regulatory Authority | logo = Enti Rregullator i Energjisë.svg | type = | foundation = | location = [[Tirana]], [[Albania]] | key_people = Petrit Ahmeti (Board Commissioner) | num_employees = | industry = [[Electric power|Electricity]] | products = | revenue = | operating_income = | parent = [[Cabinet of Albania|Government of Albania]] | net_income = | homepage = {{url|http://www.ere.gov.al}} }} The '''Energy Regulatory Authority (ERE)''' ({{lang-sq|Enti Rregullator i Energjisë|links=no}}) is an independent public entity tasked to ensure a sustainable and secure electricity supply for the [[Albania]]n consumer by establishing an operational and competitive electricity market, taking into account the consumer's interest.<ref>[http://www.monitor.al/enti-rregullator-energjise-anulloi-ndryshimin-e-cmimeve-ne-te-gjitha-nivelet-per-2017 Enti Rregullator i Energjisë anuloi ndryshimin e çmimeve në të gjitha nivelet për 2017]</ref>
ERE organizes hearings with stakeholders from the three energy operators [[Albanian Power Corporation|KESH]], [[Transmission System Operator (Albania)|OST]], and [[Electric Power Distribution Operator (Albania)|OSHEE]] to discuss price increases and tariff changes for energy production.<ref>[http://www.gazetadita.al/sot-seance-degjimore-per-energjine-cmimi-i-kerkuar-11-lekekwh KESH, OST e OSHEE prezantojnë kërkesat e tyre për çmimin e energjisë]</ref>
