{{Infobox company | name = Naturgy | logo = Naturgy.svg | type = [[S.A. (corporation)|Sociedad Anónima]] | traded_as = {{BMAD|ES0116870314|GAS}} | industry = [[Natural gas utility]] | foundation = 1991 | location = Barcelona (administrative), Madrid (legal) | key_people = [[Francisco Reynés]] <small>([[Chairman and CEO]])</small> | products = Supply, distribution and commercialisation of [[natural gas]], [[electricity generation]] and [[electricity distribution|distribution]] | revenue = €19.63 billion <small>(2010)</small><ref name="AR2010">{{cite web |url=http://portal.gasnatural.com/servlet/BlobServer?blobcol=urllink&blobtable=InformeGN&blobkey=id&blobwhere=1301393572936&blobheader=application%2Fpdf |title=Annual Report 2010 |accessdate=25 April 2011 |publisher=Gas Natural |language=Spanish}}</ref> | operating_income = €2.893 billion <small>(2010)</small><ref name="AR2010" /> | net_income = €1.201 billion <small>(2010)</small><ref name="AR2010" /> | assets = €45.34 billion <small>(end 2010)</small><ref name="AR2010" /> | equity = €12.97 billion <small>(end 2010)</small><ref name="AR2010" /> | num_employees = 18,780 <small>(end 2010)</small><ref name="AR2010" /> | homepage = [http://www.naturgy.be/ www.naturgy.be] }} [[File:Edifici Gas Natural (1).jpg|thumb|right|300px|[[Gas Natural Building]] in Barcelona,.]] '''''Naturgy Energy Group S.A.''''', formerly '''''Gas Natural Fenosa''''' ({{IPA-es|ˈɡaz natuˈɾal feˈnosa}}), is a Spanish natural gas and electrical energy utilities company, which operates primarily in [[Spain]]. The company's administrative headquarters are in [[Barcelona]], while its registered office is in [[Madrid]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.marketwatch.com/story/gas-natural-to-move-hq-to-madrid-from-barcelona-2017-10-06|title=Gas Natural to move HQ to Madrid from Barcelona|last=Lombardi|first=Pietro|work=MarketWatch|access-date=2017-10-10|language=en-US}}</ref>
It also has operations in other countries, including: [[Italy]], [[France]], [[Germany]], [[Netherlands|The Netherlands]], [[Belgium]], [[Mexico]], [[Colombia]], [[Argentina]], [[Puerto Rico]], [[Moldova]], and [[Morocco]].
==Description== The corporation's main interests are: the distribution of [[natural gas]] in Spain, Italy, and [[Latin America]]; the generation and commercialisation of electricity in the liberalised Spanish market (1997-2009);<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.expansion.com/2012/01/23/empresas/1327320803.html|title=La liberalización del sector eléctrico español |accessdate=22 July 2017 |publisher=Expansión |language=Spanish}}</ref> and the management of natural gas infrastructure and shipping transport.
Gas Natural has approximately 10,000,000 energy clients worldwide. It has around 6,700 employees, of which approximately 50% work within Spain.
The group's largest shareholders include the Spanish ''[[La Caixa]]'' bank and [[Repsol]] global energy company. {{citation needed|date=December 2016}}
''Gas Natural'' acquired [[public utility|utility]] company ''[[Unión Fenosa]]'' for around €16.8 billion in 2009.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/afxnewslimited/feeds/afx/2008/07/31/afx5276438.html|title=Gas Natural sees Fenosa deal closing in 2009|last=Ruano|first=Carlos|author2=MacInnes, Judy|date=31 July 2008|work=[[Reuters]]|publisher=[[Forbes]]|accessdate=2009-01-11}}</ref>
In June 2018, the general shareholders meeting of Gas Natural approved the change of name of the company, baptized Naturgy Energy Group.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://thecorner.eu/financial-markets/ibex/gad-natural-will-seek-purchases-and-mergers-after-becoming-naturgy/74048/|title=Gas Natural Will Seek Purchases And Mergers After Becoming Naturgy|date=28 June 2018|work=[[The Corner]]|publisher=[[The Corner]]|accessdate=}}</ref>
===Headquarters=== {{main|Gas Natural Building}} The company's administrative headquarters complex, [[Gas Natural Building]] or ''Mare Nostrum Tower'', is located in the [[La Barceloneta]] neighbourhood of the [[Ciutat Vella]] district in Barcelona. Its registered office is being moved to Madrid.
The skyscraper was designed in the [[High-tech architecture|High-tech architectural style]] by the EMBT Architects firm of architects [[Enric Miralles]] and [[Benedetta Tagliabue]], and was completed in 2005.
